<section id='s-history' class='container'>
    <h1>History - presentation</h1>
    <div>
        <h2>Capriday - history</h2>
        <div class='text-expand maxH-50'>
            <div>
                <p>Capriday was founded in 1983, at the initiative of specialists and breeders. In the early years of its establishment, as with other professional associations, goat breeders viewed this association with distrust.
                 Since 1996, Capriday has been and is increasingly in demand for technical assistance and advice for farmers and private breeders. Currently, the number of members of the association is 1400, but the number of those who contact us is very high.</p>
                <p>
                The Capriday Association is a professional organization, which brings together by free membership goat farmers, individuals or legal entities interested in carrying out technical and economic activities on improving, defending the health of goats, capitalizing on production and defending the interests of goat breeders. Capriday, operates as an organization with legal personality, having its own bank account and is self-financing, from its own sources consisting mainly of registration fees, membership fees and less from donations or sponsorships.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="text-expand-button"><b>... more</b></div>
    </div>
    <div>
        <h2>Objectives</h2>
        <div class='text-expand maxH-50'>
            <div>
                <p>The objectives of the Capriday association are:
                    - the interest of goat breeders for the numerical increase of the herds and of the production and reproduction performances, in order to increase their own income;
                    - application of technical measures regarding genetic improvement, using reproductive biotechnologies, especially artificial insemination;
                    - providing informational and technical support for diversified capitalization of goat production;
                    - supporting breeders in supply activities with goat-specific feed, medicines and consumables;
                    - organization of round tables, conferences, communications and publications on the promotion of the latest scientific and practical information in the field of goat breeding, promotion of goat production, in order to develop the taste of the population to consume meat prepared from goat meat, milk and milk cheeses goat;
                    - insurance of intermediaries and announcements between the members of the association regarding the exchange or sale of male and female reproaches;
                    - the establishment of Capriday zonal branches in all counties of the country, especially in those where a large number of goats are raised;
                    - defending the rights and interests of goat breeders, in relation to various governmental or non-governmental bodies.<p>
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="text-expand-button"><b>... more</b></div>
    </div>
    <div>
        <h2>Associates</h2>
        <div class='text-expand maxH-50'>
            <div>
                <p>Our association has been recognized by government agencies and has been a serious partner in the relationship with MADR, ANZ, ANCA, ARMRGA, etc. For these reasons, Capriday has obtained the accreditation to lead the genealogical register for most breeds bred in the country and to control the production of these goats. <p>
                 The Capriday Association is a professional organization, which brings together by free membership goat farmers, individuals or legal entities interested in carrying out technical and economic activities on improving, defending the health of goats, capitalizing on production and defending the interests of goat breeders. Capriday, operates as an organization with legal personality, having its own bank account and is self-financing, from its own sources consisting mainly of registration fees, membership fees and less from donations or sponsorships.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Since 2000, our association has been affiliated with the International Goat Association (IGA, www.goatworld.org) from which we receive valuable information support. The association has been involved in all e-conferences conducted by IGA, and has participated with concrete proposals or projects.
                </p>
