<section id='s-conditions' class='container'>
    <h1>Registration conditions</h1>
    <div class='text-expand maxH-120'>
        <div>
            <h2 class='no-fl'>Documents required for registration in the association:</h2>
            <p class='no-fl'>
                1. Adhesion - Annex 3 ROF - for newly entered members<br>
                2. Entry request COP-RG – Annex 2 ROF<br>
                3. Copy of ID card – individuals<br>
                4. CIF copy - legal entities - there must be a specified CAEN code 0145 or 0150 - otherwise the ascertaining Certificate is attached in which the activity of Raising goats is specified.<br>
                5. Updated list of animals - endorsed by the licensed veterinarian<br>
                6. Copy of Certificates of Origin (CO) for breeding goats (CO goats used for breeding must be of the same breed as goats)<br>
                7. Data protection statement - signed<br>
                8. Manufacturer's certificate - individuals<br>
            </p>
            <p>
                Completed, dated and signed documents are scanned and sent to the email address: capriday@gmail.com
                 After receiving the documents, the invoice will be issued, which will be paid into the account * specifying the name of the registered person.
            </p>
            <p>
            Each newly registered owner will be contacted by telephone by the COP controller to arrange a visit to the farm: inventory and crediting of goat herds. The breeder's rights and obligations will also be brought to the attention of the breeder.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
